.TH MALDET "1" "March 2026" "Linux Malware Detect v2.0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
maldet \- Linux malware scanner for shared hosting environments
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B maldet
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B maldet
(Linux Malware Detect) is an open\-source malware scanner designed for
Linux shared hosting environments.
It provides multi\-stage detection using MD5 and SHA\-256 hashes, HEX patterns,
compound signatures (csig), statistical analysis, native YARA rules, and
optional ClamAV integration.
Detected threats can be quarantined, cleaned, or reported via email,
Slack, Telegram, and Discord.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Scanning
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-scan\-all\fR \fIPATH\fR
Scan all files in \fIPATH\fR (default: /home).
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-scan\-recent\fR \fIPATH\fR \fIDAYS\fR
Scan files created or modified in the last \fIDAYS\fR days (default: 7).
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\-list\fR \fIFILE\fR
Scan files listed in \fIFILE\fR, one path per line.
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-background\fR
Run the scan operation in the background. May appear anywhere in the command line.
.SS Filters
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-include\-regex\fR \fIREGEX\fR
Include only paths matching POSIX extended regular expression.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-x\fR, \fB\-\-exclude\-regex\fR \fIREGEX\fR
Exclude paths matching POSIX extended regular expression.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.SS Monitoring
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-monitor\fR \fIUSERS\fR|\fIPATHS\fR|\fIFILE\fR|\fIRELOAD\fR
Start inotify real\-time monitoring.
By default, the supervisor runs in the foreground and holds the terminal.
Use \fB\-b\fR before \fB\-\-monitor\fR to daemonize: \fBmaldet \-b \-m users\fR.
\fBusers\fR monitors homedirs of UIDs above \fBinotify_minuid\fR.
\fBPATHS\fR accepts a comma\-separated list.
\fBFILE\fR reads paths from a file.
\fBreload\fR triggers a configuration reload.
.TP
\fB\-k\fR, \fB\-\-kill\-monitor\fR
Stop the inotify monitoring service.
Sends SIGTERM to the supervisor for a clean shutdown; escalates to SIGKILL
after a 10-second timeout if the process does not exit.
.SS Quarantine and Restore
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quarantine\fR \fISCANID\fR
Quarantine all hits from scan report \fISCANID\fR.
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-clean\fR \fISCANID\fR
Attempt to clean malware from files in scan report \fISCANID\fR.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-restore\fR \fIFILE\fR|\fISCANID\fR
Restore a quarantined file or all files from \fISCANID\fR.
.TP
\fB\-qd\fR \fIPATH\fR
Override the quarantine directory for this run.
\fIPATH\fR must exist or the command exits with an error.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.SS Reporting
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-report\fR [\fISCANID\fR|\fBlist\fR]
View a scan report.
Use \fBlist\fR to show all reports.
Combine with \fB\-\-format\fR and \fB\-\-mailto\fR for output control.
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fBtext\fR|\fBjson\fR|\fBhtml\fR
Set report output format for \fB\-e\fR/\fB\-\-report\fR (default: text).
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-\-mailto\fR \fIADDRESS\fR
Email the report to the specified address instead of stdout.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-\-json\-report\fR [\fISCANID\fR|\fBlist\fR]
Shorthand for \fB\-\-report \-\-format json\fR.
Output a JSON\-formatted scan report for the given \fISCANID\fR.
Use \fBlist\fR to output all scan reports as a JSON array.
Supports both TSV and legacy plaintext sessions.
.TP
\fB\-\-alert\-daily\fR (also: \fB\-\-monitor\-report\fR)
Generate a digest alert summarizing inotify monitor activity.
Requires monitor mode to be running.
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-log\fR
Display the event log.
.SS Updates
.TP
\fB\-u\fR, \fB\-\-update\-sigs\fR [\fB\-\-force\fR]
Update malware signatures from rfxn.com.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-update\-ver\fR [\fB\-\-force\fR|\fB\-\-beta\fR]
Update the LMD installation to the latest version.
.TP
\fB\-\-cron\-sigup\fR
Perform a signature update for the independent cron job.
Serialized with \fBflock\fR to prevent concurrent runs.
Includes a random 0\-120s sleep to avoid upstream stampede.
Internal use only \(em invoked by
.IR /etc/cron.d/maldet\-sigup ;
not intended for direct invocation.
.SS Other
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-checkout\fR \fIFILE\fR
Upload a suspected malware sample to rfxn.com for analysis.
.TP
\fB\-\-mkpubpaths\fR
Create per\-user pub/ data directories for non\-root scan operations.
Requires \fBscan_user_access=1\fR in conf.maldet.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-purge\fR
Clear logs, quarantine queue, session, and temporary data.
.TP
\fB\-U\fR, \fB\-\-user\fR \fIUSER\fR
Run as the specified user (for viewing reports or restoring quarantine).
.TP
\fB\-co\fR, \fB\-\-config\-option\fR \fIVAR\fR=\fIVAL\fR[,\fIVAR\fR=\fIVAL\fR,...]
Override configuration options at runtime.
.TP
\fB\-\-web\-proxy\fR \fIIP\fR:\fIPORT\fR
Set HTTP/HTTPS proxy for all remote connections.
.TP
\fB\-hscan\fR, \fB\-\-hook\-scan\fR
Scan a single file supplied by a ModSecurity \fIinspectFile\fR hook.
Used internally by \fBhookscan.sh\fR; not intended for direct invocation.
May appear anywhere in the command line.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Display version information.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display usage information.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success; no malware found.
.TP
.B 1
Error or invalid arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Malware hits detected.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/conf.maldet
User configuration file.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/internals.conf
Internal paths, binary discovery, and URL definitions.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/compat.conf
Backward compatibility variable mappings.
.TP
.B /usr/local/maldetect/internals/lmd.lib.sh
Core library sourcing hub \(em sources all sub-libraries in dependency order.
.TP
.B /usr/local/maldetect/internals/lmd_*.sh
Decomposed function libraries: lmd_init, lmd_config, lmd_scan, lmd_engine,
lmd_clamav, lmd_yara, lmd_sigs, lmd_quarantine, lmd_session, lmd_monitor,
lmd_update.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/alert_lib.sh
Shared alerting library (email, Slack, Telegram, Discord delivery).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/lmd_alert.sh
LMD-specific alert functions (data preparation, rendering pipeline).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/alert/
Alert template directory (HTML, text, and messaging templates).
Custom overrides go in
.I alert/custom.d/
and are preserved across upgrades.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/tlog_lib.sh
Shared incremental log reading library.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/internals/elog_lib.sh
Shared structured event logging library.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/
Signature directory (MD5, SHA\-256, HEX, CSIG, YARA, ClamAV).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/csig.dat
Compound signature rules (multi\-pattern boolean logic).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/custom.csig.dat
User\-defined compound signature rules.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/sha256v2.dat
SHA\-256 hash signatures (HASH:SIZE:{SHA256}sig.name.N).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/custom.sha256.dat
User\-defined SHA\-256 hash signatures.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sigs/rfxn.hsb
ClamAV SHA\-256 hash signature database (ClamAV >= 0.97).
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/quarantine/
Quarantine storage for detected malware.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/sess/session.tsv.*
TSV\-format scan session data files containing a 19\-field metadata header
and 11\-field hit records.
Canonical format as of v2.0.1.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/logs/event_log
Event log.
.TP
.I /etc/cron.daily/maldet
Daily cron job for automated scanning and updates.
.TP
.I /etc/cron.weekly/maldet\-watchdog
Weekly watchdog for fallback signature updates.
.TP
.I /etc/cron.d/maldet\-sigup
Independent signature update cron job (interval set by \fBsigup_interval\fR).
.TP
.I /etc/sysconfig/maldet " or " /etc/default/maldet
System\-level configuration overrides.
.TP
.I /usr/local/maldetect/monitor_paths.extra
Line-separated file of additional paths to add to the inotify watch list.
Managed independently of
.BR conf.maldet .
See
.B monitor_paths_extra
in the CONFIGURATION section.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is loaded from
.I conf.maldet
and can be overridden by system files and the
.B \-co
flag.
Key variables by category:
.PP
.B Alerting:
.BR email_alert ,
.BR email_addr ,
.BR email_format ,
.BR smtp_relay ,
.BR smtp_from ,
.BR smtp_user ,
.BR smtp_pass ,
.BR slack_alert ,
.BR slack_token ,
.BR slack_channels ,
.BR telegram_alert ,
.BR telegram_bot_token ,
.BR telegram_channel_id ,
.BR discord_alert ,
.BR discord_webhook_url .
.PP
.B Scanning:
.BR scan_hashtype ,
.BR scan_clamscan ,
.BR scan_csig ,
.BR scan_yara ,
.BR scan_yara_scope ,
.BR scan_workers ,
.BR scan_hexdepth ,
.BR scan_max_filesize ,
.BR scan_find_timeout ,
.BR scan_cpunice ,
.BR scan_ignore_root ,
.BR string_length_scan .
.PP
.B Quarantine:
.BR quarantine_hits ,
.BR quarantine_clean ,
.BR quarantine_suspend_user ,
.BR quarantine_suspend_user_minuid .
.PP
.B Monitoring:
.BR default_monitor_mode ,
.BR inotify_minuid ,
.BR inotify_docroot ,
.BR inotify_sleep ,
.BR inotify_reloadtime ,
.BR inotify_cpunice ,
.BR digest_interval ,
.BR digest_escalate_hits ,
.BR monitor_paths_extra .
.PP
.B Maintenance:
.BR autoupdate_signatures ,
.BR autoupdate_version ,
.BR autoupdate_version_hashed ,
.BR sigup_interval ,
.BR cron_prune_days ,
.BR cron_daily_scan ,
.BR scan_days .
.PP
.B autoupdate_version_hashed
validates the SHA\-256 hash of installed LMD executables against known good
upstream values on each update check.
Falls back to MD5 verification if sha256sum is unavailable.
Forces reinstallation on mismatch.
Default: 1.
.PP
.B sigup_interval
sets the interval in hours for automatic signature update checks via
the independent cron job
.RI ( /etc/cron.d/maldet\-sigup ).
This runs separately from
.I cron.daily
and is idempotent with
.BR "maldet \-u" .
Set to 0 to disable the independent cron job.
Valid range: 1\-24.
Default: 6.
.PP
.B scan_hashtype
selects the hash algorithm for file\-hash signature matching (stage 1).
Values: \fBauto\fR (use SHA\-256 if CPU has hardware acceleration, else MD5),
\fBsha256\fR (always SHA\-256),
\fBmd5\fR (always MD5; preserves performance on older CPUs without SHA\-NI).
Default: auto.
.PP
.B scan_csig
enables compound signature (csig) scanning.
Compound signatures support multi\-pattern boolean logic (AND/OR/threshold),
case\-insensitive matching, wide (UTF\-16LE) matching, and bounded gap wildcards.
Runs in native mode only (not with ClamAV).
Default: 1.
.PP
.B scan_workers
sets the number of parallel workers for native MD5, SHA\-256, HEX, and CSIG scan passes.
A value of \fBauto\fR (default) uses automatic detection: 2 workers per CPU core, up to 8.
Set to 1 for single\-threaded operation.
Maximum value: 8.
.PP
.B scan_find_timeout
sets the maximum execution time in seconds for the
.BR find (1)
file list generation phase.
A value of 0 disables the timeout.
Values between 1 and 59 are silently ignored (minimum is 60).
Default: 0.
.PP
.B scan_days
sets the number of days to look back for recently modified files during
daily cron scans.
This value is passed as the \fIDAYS\fR argument to
.BR "maldet \-r" .
Default: 1.
.PP
.B email_format
sets the format for email alerts.
Values: \fBtext\fR (plain text only), \fBhtml\fR (HTML with text fallback),
\fBboth\fR (multipart alternative with both formats).
Default: html.
.PP
.B smtp_relay
sets an SMTP relay for email delivery instead of the local MTA.
When set, emails are sent via this relay using curl.
Examples: \fBsmtps://smtp.gmail.com:465\fR, \fBsmtp://relay.example.com:587\fR.
Requires \fBsmtp_from\fR to be set.
.PP
.B smtp_from
sets the sender address for SMTP relay delivery.
Required when \fBsmtp_relay\fR is set.
.PP
.B smtp_user
and
.B smtp_pass
set SMTP authentication credentials for relay delivery.
.PP
.B session_legacy_compat
controls generation of legacy plaintext session files alongside TSV.
Values: \fBauto\fR (detect old\-format sessions, enable if found \(em default),
\fB1\fR (always generate plaintext),
\fB0\fR (TSV only).
Default: auto.
.PP
.B ClamAV Signature Validation
.PP
When ClamAV is installed, LMD validates signature files via
.B clamscan \-d
against a staging directory before deploying them to ClamAV data
directories.
If validation fails, existing LMD signatures are removed from the
ClamAV path to protect ClamAV from loading malformed databases.
The
.B SIGUSR2
reload signal to
.B clamd
is only sent when at least one ClamAV data directory passes validation.
This prevents malformed signature updates from breaking ClamAV (issue #467).
.PP
.B digest_interval
sets the period between automatic digest summary alerts in monitor mode.
Accepts a numeric value with a unit suffix:
.B Nh
(hours),
.B Nm
(minutes),
.B Nd
(days).
Set to
.B 0
to disable periodic digests.
Default: 24h.
.PP
.B digest_escalate_hits
sets a hit-count threshold for immediate escalation alerts in monitor mode.
When the number of new hits detected since the last digest exceeds this value,
an alert is sent immediately rather than waiting for the next digest interval.
Set to
.B 0
to disable escalation.
Default: 0.
.PP
.B monitor_paths_extra
is the path to a line-separated file of additional paths to add to the
inotify watch list.
Entries in this file are merged with the primary watch list on every
configuration reload, allowing paths to be added without modifying
.B conf.maldet
or restarting the monitor.
Default: /usr/local/maldetect/monitor_paths.extra.
.PP
See
.I conf.maldet
for the full list with descriptions.
.SH MONITOR MODE
The monitor command runs a supervisor process that manages an
.BR inotifywait (1)
child watching for file create, modify, and move events.
.PP
By default,
.B maldet \-m users
runs in the foreground, keeping the terminal occupied.
Use
.B maldet \-b \-m users
to daemonize the supervisor and return immediately.
The
.B \-b
flag may appear anywhere on the command line.
.PP
The supervisor automatically recovers from
.B inotifywait
crashes using exponential backoff (2, 4, 8, 16, 32 seconds).
After three consecutive failures the supervisor exits with a logged error.
.PP
.B maldet \-k
sends SIGTERM to the running supervisor for a clean shutdown.
If the process does not exit within 10 seconds, SIGKILL is sent.
.PP
A periodic digest summary alert is sent every
.B digest_interval
(default: 24h).
If the number of new hits since the last digest exceeds
.B digest_escalate_hits
(default: 0, disabled), an immediate escalation alert is sent regardless of the interval.
.PP
Additional watch paths can be supplied without modifying
.B conf.maldet
by listing them (one per line) in the file pointed to by
.BR monitor_paths_extra .
These are merged with the primary path list on every cycle reload.
.PP
.B Behavioral change \(em ignore_inotify entries are now treated as literal paths.
ERE metacharacters
.RI ( . ,
.IR * ,
.IR + ,
etc.) are automatically escaped before the path is used as a pattern.
Users who previously relied on ERE regex patterns in
.B ignore_inotify
should update their entries to use literal path strings.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan all files under user web roots:
.B maldet \-a /home/?/public_html
.TP
Scan recent files with auto\-quarantine and YARA:
.B maldet \-co quarantine_hits=1,scan_yara=1 \-r /home/?/public_html 2
.TP
View the most recent scan report:
.B maldet \-e
.TP
List all scan reports:
.B maldet \-e list
.TP
Output a scan report as JSON:
.B maldet \-\-json\-report SCANID
.TP
List all reports as JSON:
.B maldet \-\-json\-report list
.TP
Quarantine all hits from a scan:
.B maldet \-q SCANID
.TP
Start real\-time inotify monitoring (foreground):
.B maldet \-m users
.TP
Start real\-time inotify monitoring (background daemon):
.B maldet \-b \-m users
